{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BeR3JQpuCkEQC4fQ3dKf17","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is the `seed-hosts-repair` case. The precondition set up an index fixture and the case is about a node that failed to rejoin the cluster. \n\nLooking at the parameters:\n- `BENCH_PARAM_CLUSTER_PREFIX`: \"es-cluster\"\n- `BENCH_PARAM_HTTP_SERVICE_NAME`: \"es-http\"\n- `BENCH_PARAM_CURL_POD_NAME`: \"curl-test\"\n- `BENCH_PARAM_CONFIGMAP_NAME`: \"es-config\"\n- `BENCH_PARAM_INDEX_NAME`: \"app-data\"\n- `BENCH_PARAM_EXPECTED_NODE_COUNT`: \"3\"\n- `BENCH_PARAM_FAULT_EXPECTED_NODES`: \"2\"\n\nSo we're expecting 3 nodes normally (es-cluster-0, 1, 2), dropping to 2 during the fault scenario. The precondition was checking for 9 running pods, which seems higher than just the cluster nodes. Let me find the actual seed-hosts-repair case definition to understand what's being tested.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1253,"cache_read_input_tokens":37343,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1253},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"25f65c27-c4e3-4259-a645-5a43bc6837a5","uuid":"586118f7-40f8-4ca6-8fc1-ea8ae60150e1","request_id":"req_011CcM1hd5K1tuZbbzmuF7fG"}
