{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GqdvhMidsqyvrmDJPGgEjz","type":"tool_result","content":"145\t    execution branch from ``run_flow.py`` is not carried forward.\n146\t\n147\t    For each unit, the probe tests whether the target state already holds:\n148\t\n149\t    * probe **passes** -> state already present, apply is skipped.\n150\t    * probe **fails** + ``on_probe_fail=\"skip\"`` (the default, used by setup\n151\t      units) -> the \"not yet present\" signal is expected, so apply runs to\n152\t      establish the state, then verify.\n153\t    * probe **fails** + ``on_probe_fail=\"error\"`` -> a readiness/convergence\n154\t      gate the apply cannot satisfy. The probe is retried up to\n155\t      ``verify_retries`` times (``verify_interval_sec`` apart) to let a slow\n156\t      cluster converge; the failure becomes fatal only after that budget.\n157\t\n158\t    Retries verify up to ``verify_retries`` times with\n159\t    ``verify_interval_sec`` between attempts. All command output is\n160\t    appended to *log_path*.\n161\t\n162\t    ``phase_timeout_sec`` bounds the wall-clock time of the whole phase\n163\t    (``None`` = unbounded, the default for callers that do not opt in).\n164\t    When set, each command's timeout is capped to the remaining budget and\n165\t    the phase aborts as soon as the deadline passes -- this is what makes\n166\t    ``--setup-timeout`` (``settings.precondition_timeout_sec``) actually\n167\t    bound the precondition phase, mirroring the oracle's wall-clock cap.\n168\t\n169\t    Returns\n170\t    -------\n171\t    dict\n172\t        Keys: ``ok`` (bool), ``units`` (list[dict] of per-unit outcomes),\n173\t        ``output`` (str), ``timed_out`` (bool -- True if the phase budget\n174\t        was exhausted).\n175\t    \"\"\"\n176\t    import os\n177\t    import subprocess\n178\t\n179\t    log_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n180\t    env = {**os.environ, **role_bindings, **(env_vars or {})}\n181\t    all_output: list[str] = []\n182\t    unit_outcomes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n183\t    overall_ok = True\n184\t\n185\t    # Wall-clock deadline for the whole phase. ``None`` means unbounded.\n186\t    deadline = (time.monotonic() + phase_timeout_sec) if phase_timeout_sec else None\n187\t    timed_out = False\n188\t\n189\t    def _exec(cmd_entry: dict[str, Any], phase: str, unit_id: str):\n190\t        \"\"\"Run one command, capping its timeout to the remaining phase budget.\n191\t\n192\t        Returns the subprocess return code, or ``None`` if the command did\n193\t        not complete (error or timeout). A timeout that occurs once the phase\n194\t        budget is the binding constraint sets the enclosing ``timed_out`` flag.\n195\t        \"\"\"\n196\t        nonlocal timed_out\n197\t        cmd = cmd_entry[\"command\"]\n198\t        # Explicit timeout_sec wins; otherwise infer from the command verb\n199\t        # (wait/rollout get minutes) instead of the flat command_timeout_sec.\n200\t        base_to = cmd_entry.get(\"timeout_sec\") or _default_timeout_for_command(cmd, phase)\n201\t        cmd_to = base_to\n202\t        capped = False  # True once the phase budget is the binding constraint.\n203\t        if deadline is not None:\n204\t            remaining = deadline - time.monotonic()"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"25f65c27-c4e3-4259-a645-5a43bc6837a5","uuid":"287a099a-992a-4201-a846-76598073100e","timestamp":"2026-06-23T22:54:44.681Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/karma/runtime/case.py","content":"    execution branch from ``run_flow.py`` is not carried forward.\n\n    For each unit, the probe tests whether the target state already holds:\n\n    * probe **passes** -> state already present, apply is skipped.\n    * probe **fails** + ``on_probe_fail=\"skip\"`` (the default, used by setup\n      units) -> the \"not yet present\" signal is expected, so apply runs to\n      establish the state, then verify.\n    * probe **fails** + ``on_probe_fail=\"error\"`` -> a readiness/convergence\n      gate the apply cannot satisfy. The probe is retried up to\n      ``verify_retries`` times (``verify_interval_sec`` apart) to let a slow\n      cluster converge; the failure becomes fatal only after that budget.\n\n    Retries verify up to ``verify_retries`` times with\n    ``verify_interval_sec`` between attempts. All command output is\n    appended to *log_path*.\n\n    ``phase_timeout_sec`` bounds the wall-clock time of the whole phase\n    (``None`` = unbounded, the default for callers that do not opt in).\n    When set, each command's timeout is capped to the remaining budget and\n    the phase aborts as soon as the deadline passes -- this is what makes\n    ``--setup-timeout`` (``settings.precondition_timeout_sec``) actually\n    bound the precondition phase, mirroring the oracle's wall-clock cap.\n\n    Returns\n    -------\n    dict\n        Keys: ``ok`` (bool), ``units`` (list[dict] of per-unit outcomes),\n        ``output`` (str), ``timed_out`` (bool -- True if the phase budget\n        was exhausted).\n    \"\"\"\n    import os\n    import subprocess\n\n    log_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    env = {**os.environ, **role_bindings, **(env_vars or {})}\n    all_output: list[str] = []\n    unit_outcomes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    overall_ok = True\n\n    # Wall-clock deadline for the whole phase. ``None`` means unbounded.\n    deadline = (time.monotonic() + phase_timeout_sec) if phase_timeout_sec else None\n    timed_out = False\n\n    def _exec(cmd_entry: dict[str, Any], phase: str, unit_id: str):\n        \"\"\"Run one command, capping its timeout to the remaining phase budget.\n\n        Returns the subprocess return code, or ``None`` if the command did\n        not complete (error or timeout). A timeout that occurs once the phase\n        budget is the binding constraint sets the enclosing ``timed_out`` flag.\n        \"\"\"\n        nonlocal timed_out\n        cmd = cmd_entry[\"command\"]\n        # Explicit timeout_sec wins; otherwise infer from the command verb\n        # (wait/rollout get minutes) instead of the flat command_timeout_sec.\n        base_to = cmd_entry.get(\"timeout_sec\") or _default_timeout_for_command(cmd, phase)\n        cmd_to = base_to\n        capped = False  # True once the phase budget is the binding constraint.\n        if deadline is not None:\n            remaining = deadline - time.monotonic()","numLines":60,"startLine":145,"totalLines":983}}}
